Nov 15 2009 	Great value on the strip!	I stayed at the Monte Carlo in August of 2009 with my best friend. First time to Vegas!We booked with Tripcentral.ca and flew out of Toronto via Sunwing. Included in our package were free tickets to KA.The Monte Carlo may not be as big as the other strip hotels, but upon first glance you can appreciate the understated elegance. The lobby is lovely with fresh flower arrangements. Check in was a relatively painless procedure.The room was clean and quiet. Two double beds and a decent bathroom. To cut down on the &quot;getting ready&quot; time I used the shower at the gym/spa so my friend could have the bathroom to herself. What a deal!!! I paid $39 for a 3-day pass that included use of the gym, sauna, whirlpool &amp; cool plunge, a sitting room with complimentary juice/bottled water/fruit, etc. I used their shampoo, conditioner, soap, shaving gel, razors, hair dryer, curling iron, hairspray, etc. It was like this private little peace of heaven in the middle of Vegas. Very relaxing. The gym had a good selection of cardio equipment and weights and it was not busy. It was a really great way to start each crazy Vegas day! The pool area was nice. The usual towel/reservation thing happens. I didn't gamble much, but the casino was fun. No problems getting drinks the first night, but after that I gave up. The lack of waitresses on the floor was one of my only complaints. I felt bad for them because they were really trying to keep up with the demand. The buffet was good. We had the breakfast buffet twice and at $18/person we made the most of it!!! I tried grits for the first time!All in all, I don't think you can beat the value of the Monte Carlo. The location is great and the facilities are very nice. There is a Duece stop right outside the Monte Carlo which makes getting around the strip a lot easier on your poor tired feet (abandon your vanity and wear comfortable shoes!!!!).	
Nov 14 2009 	Good quality hotel with "off the strip" prices!	We stayed 5 nights at this hotel and would stay here again. Its next door to Hotel New York New York and across the road from the Coca Cola bottle (20feet high) were the Tix4today office is for half price show tickets. Tix4today is THE place to buy all show tickets except Caesars Palace. The Monorail is a bit of a walk through the MGM Grand Hotel but it is much quicker especially if you use it to go to Fremont Experience (NOT to be missed!). The Deuce bus, outside the Cola Cola bottle is $7 for the day but does take 45 mins to get to Fremont Experience although you see lots more from the bus. Trolley bus no longer operates!The food at the cafe restaurant at the Hotel Monte Carlo was excellent and at reasonable prices for the standard. (we had no time to try their buffet) Some of the better known larger hotels were a disappointment for food and overpriced. Best buffet is at the Bellagio Hotel but note that dinner prices start at 3pm! Don't get caught out with the Gelato at $16 at Caesars Palace!Each hotel offers from $5 upwards to join their Players Clubs for their casinos. its free to join , You get a card with the money on and as you play points are added to your card for prizes even room rate specials, IF you spend alot.Las Vegas has something for everyone, each hotel is a mini &quot;Disneyworld&quot; so allow plenty of time and a good pair of comfortable shoes!	
