Oct 25 2009 	Perfect Hotel for our vacation!	Myself, my father and brother stayed at the Monte Carlo for 4 nights October 19-23 and couldn't have asked for a better hotel. The hotel is located between the city center (which is currently under construction) and New York, New York. There are many restaurants, nightclubs and shopping within walking distance.Our room was on the 18th floor and had an awesome view of the pool and new City Center. The room was well kept, clean and had everything we needed (there is hair dryer and iron/board in room). All that really matters is that you have a bed - you are in vegas!! if you want a nice quiet place - stay home!!The staff at the Monte Carlo are awesome! Anything you need (extra towels, water, matches... etc.) they have it to you in no time and with a smile. They even took 2 long distance phone calls off our bill because I didn't get through ($15 per call - buy a phone card!!) check - in and check out was a breeze. The only thing i didn't like was the $9.50 per day resort fee. It included bottles of water in the room daily and printing of boarding passes.I have been to vegas a few times before, but my father and brother never have, so we rented a car and I took them to the Hoover Dam. We stopped at a few of the older historic casinos and hotels on the way. Make sure you eat or pack a lunch before you get to the Hoover Dam. We paid $45.00 for 3 burgers &amp; fries there!! The casino at the monte wasnt too crowded most of the time, which is nice not to have to wait for a table or machine. We did win a little ( enough to pay for 3 tickets for 2 shows, and most of our meals) which was a bonus.Jubilee (at Bally's)- seen it 3 times now. Fantastic cabaret style show. Definately worth it. Ask cab drivers for coupon books - we got the $92.50 seats for $35.00!! We wanted tickets for the Beatles Love but it was sold out, so we saw Human Nature by Smokey Robinson at the Imperial Palace. Great show, very lively.Anyhow, I've stayed at many of the big properties in vegas, like the MGM Grand, Paris, etc., and the Monte Carlo is definately a great place to stay, we will go back for sure.One tip I can leave for people is: have a good time in vegas dont get wrapped up by the reviews and whatnot. you vacation is what you make it. If you get upset at every little thing - just stay home!!!	
