Oct 22 2009 	Go -- if only for the pools!	Spent 2 nights at the Monte Carlo in late June. One of the hottest weekends hitting around 106. In JUNE!The hotel was nice, clean and what you could expect. The location was ok, but with the sprawling properties combined with the construction on the strip, we pretty much stayed put.The only issues we had with the hotel was the temperature of the rooms. We could not seem to get the a/c cool enough at night and had trouble sleeping. Also, we thought we were hearing hallway, or neighboring room conversations, but realized that the maid had left the radio on the lowest volume. A little irritating, but easy fix once we turned off the radio.THE BEST PART IS THE POOLS! Although there was a good crowd and trouble finding a seat if you were outside any later than 9am, there was plenty of water to play in and around. The lazy river was a blast! Buy an intertube at Rite Aid or the ABC Store instead of renting at the hotel. Also, bring your own beverages into the pool to save cash. The wave pool was a serious party with DJ, though the playlist could use some better rotation. I think they only played about 15 songs on a continuous loop.Another cool thing, which I suspect all hotels are going to be picking up on...you can sign up for hotel deals and discount through text messaging. We were getting offers for BOGO dinners and drinks for all the hotels in the company (includes NYNY and Caesars).We would definitely come back to the Monte.	
