Oct 20 2009 	Simply an amazing experience.	I arrived at the Monte Carlo around 10:30PM and it took about 10 minutes to check in with no problems, oh and I love hearing &quot;You already paid for the room, we don't need to have your card on file, unless you want movies or something.&quot; We get up to the room and its HUGE! (2 Queen beds a non-smoking). The bathroom is big as well, nice tile floor and marble counter, shower head could have been updated but still very nice waterfall style. We had a great view of the New York New York and the Excalibur.We went to the pool the next day, the lazy river is pretty cool, although $12.95 for a inner-tube is kind of steep, but you can just go in without one. The other pool is nice as well, as is the jacuzzi.The service is what made this place amazing, I had a shirt on bed that I left there, I left the room to get a bite to eat, I come back and guess what the SHIRT IS FOLDED on the bed, I've never had a maid do that before.The food-court is open 24 hours but kind of pricey, for instance a foot long turkey sandwich and Subway was $9.00. If you ask the front desk for coupons upon check-in however, you can get a free soda or something with purchase.The one complaint I had was that the air conditioning unit in the room was in-wall and controlled by a thermostat in the room, you can set it to 60 and fan Hi, and it takes a while to get cold but its not loud so I guess that's good.Could use some more TV channels and also about the noise from the pool DJ, I had a room on the other side and didn't hear it. I do admit the walls are kind of thin, you can hear people talking and doors shutting but its ok, it won't keep you up because the beds are amazing.Overall, this is one of the best hotels I've stayed in, I've stayed in luxury hotels in New York and San Francisco among other places and so far only few have compared to this one.	
Oct 20 2009 	Third time lucky but then you get what you pay for	The Monte Carlo is a good on strip hotel, not fantastic, not awful, but good. On checkin we were given a smoking room with two Queen size beds and neither myself or my partner smoke, the room was tainted by the smell of cigarettes and wasn't ideal. I called the front desk and they moved us to a non smoking floor immediately. Our second room albeit slightly better had two Queen size beds again which to be frank is useless to a couple and takes up a lot of the floor space. I called the front desk and asked to be moved again to a room with a single King size bed. The front desk told me they couldn't do this for the first evening but were able to the next day. Finally, the next day we got a room that was ideal, a king size bed, and plenty of floor space for luggage, shopping etc. Throughout the experience I do have to say the front desk were accommodating and helpful at every turn.As for the remainder, the Pub has had a makeover and the Beer Towers have gone which is a bit of a bind as they made the old micro brewery worth a visit. I didn't use the pools but did go out there a couple of times, unfortunately you don't get much sun late on in the afternoon as the new building adjacent do their best to block out the sunlight. The Casino itself was ok, free craps lessons every day at 11. Occasional $5 blackjack tables for those gambling on a budget but I have to give special mention to Gail, one of the blackjack dealers. Her friendly demeanor really made playing at the table a pleasure, she introduced us to several people from all over the world and the table had a great atmosphere.There's also a Starbucks at the back of the Casino for those in need of a morning coffee, one thing I would say is the queues here get pretty big and you may have a wait so if you need a fix it might be quicker to go to NYNY next door.All in all, the location is on strip and pretty good but not central, the cleanliness and service are as you would expect from any hotel. My only gripe would be the rooms as they could probably do with being touched up but overall, we booked 90 days in advance and so got a good discount and on the strength of that it was a great value for money location and I wouldn't have any qualms staying in this hotel again.	
