Oct 11 2009 	Central and easy to navigate	Stayed in the Monte Carlo for 4 nights during a 2 week trip around the US. First impressions is the hotel is very nice and everything is on your doorstep, either within the hotel or just outside. Check in staff were incrediably slow, but conceirge on future visits about missing rooms items was very helpful and prompt. Rooms were spacious but dark and bathrooms were fine. We found the lack of coffee makers and bar fridges a sign that we were being forced to stay out of the rooms to spend money. There is a $4.99 fee on the atms downstairs which was a shock, but I think within the casino region that is probably the norm.Cleaning left a bit to be desired, for example when the cleaner couldn't reach a corner of the bed to put the duvet flat it was left. This may be due to the huge volume of rooms they have to clean and there isn't the time to make the finishing touches. The room service trays were left for well over 24hours on our floor, which we thought was unacceptable particularly as the guests had left half eaten food uncovered.Buffet in the hotel was lovely with very friendly staff and was great value. Casino staff were fantastic and had endless patience. The bar had the opposite and we weren't treated as if they wanted us there (once they decided to serve us). Be careful with the baggage storage as bags are not kept together and we had to go back to the hotel from the airport when we realised they had not put all the luggage into the taxi.	
