Oct 8 2009 	Excellent value and service right on the strip	We stayed at the Monte Carlo for a mini-vacation. We absolutely loved the hotel. The one thing that I noticed was that there was no smokey smell that is very apparent in other hotels around the strip. This is an excellent value for a nice hotel right in the middle of the strip. We really like the location - you can walk right out of the hotel and be right on the strip. It isn't an over-the-top hotel like most of the ones that you find on the strip on Vegas. The hotel room are very clean - and smell clean too! No smells of cigarettes that you get at other hotels. I would definitely stay here again. Their players club program is great too - you can accumulate points at the Monte Carlo, MGM, Bellagio and a bunch of other affiliated hotels on the strip. If you're looking for an over-the-top hotel experience like Bellagio or Venetian, then the Monte Carlo probably isn't for you. If you're looking for a nicely appointed, clean smelling, fairly reasonable hotel right on the strip then the Monte Carlo is where you want to stay.	
