Sep 15 2009 	Great stay	Visited Las Vegas and stayed at the Monte Carlo. Great location, right on the strip close (as close as you can be) to shopping and other casinos. For those who haven't visited Vegas before, things are a lot further than they appear on the map so be prepared.After waiting for over an hour for a shuttle (take a taxi, with two people or more it was cheaper than a shuttle and takes a lot less time) we arrived at the Monte Carlo. Check in was smooth but upon arrival in our room my wife had an allergic reaction to some cleaning product that left a very strong smell. We went back to the front desk and asked to switch rooms. They were more than accomodating and quickly got us another room.&gt;Rooms were large and clean. Beds were comfortable and bathroom was very nice. They were doing some construction nearby, but noise wasn't too big of a factor. Had some neighbors that kept us up late one night, but it is Vegas so I imagine that happens all the time. Elevators were quick and we never had to wait.&gt;Casino was large and had table games, slots, sports betting, ect. Waitresses provided drinks regularly. Nice atmosphere all around.&gt;Pool, lazy river, wave pool were AWESOME. Great way to cool off on a hot, hot Nevada day. Drinks by the pool are expensive.&gt;Restaurants in the hotel are good, nothing too spectacular. Lots to choose from though from buffet to steak house to fast food and everything in between.&gt;Shops were okay in the hotel, we didn't browse in them too much.All in all, a very good stay. Friendly staff, great casino and beautiful pool. Would recommend.	
Sep 14 2009 	No complaints at all	Although the MC would not be rated a 5-star resort, our group of eight could find very little to complain about.The pool area had plenty of lounges and good service from the waitstaff. You might have a little trouble finding a &quot;prime&quot; lounge if you got to the area during peek times. Saturday and Sunday had larger crowds than Friday and Monday did, which is for obvious reasons. Even though signs state that you cannot bring in outside beverages, this was rarely enforced. Just keep out the glass and coolers.The food court provided an inexpensive meal option for a quick breakfast of lunch.The casino never felt crowded or stressed. It was easy to move about machines and tables. The dealers were very willing to offer tips and suggestions to the inexperienced betters in our group.Location of this resort is perfect for exploring the strip and will be a prime spot when the City Center opens.We would gladly stay here again, especially at the right price	
