Sep 9 2009 	Would not stay here again	The Monte Carlo was not awful, but our room smelled like industrial cleaner and the sheets did not fit the bed. The pool, which is advertised as being huge, was a serious disappointment--it is tiny compared to others in the area. Plus, the water was disgustingly dirty and a DJ was blaring tunes all day long. It was not a relaxing scene, more of a Spring Break feel. There is only one main pool and it was so crowded that we could not even find a chair--we would have had to sit on the cement. The pool guy recommended we walk two hotels down to Excalibur and use their pool, which we did. Their pool was fantastic-had an adults only section, 3-4 pools and tons of chairs. What was I paying Monte Carlo for if I had to walk 25 minutes down the Strip to use someone else’s pool? The worst aspect of the hotel is the food. The restaurants are TERRIBLE!!! We spent our last evening at the hotel's steak restaurant, Brand, which is pretty pricey. Our entire meal tasted as if it was smoked, even the asparagus. All dishes, including salads, are made for two. What in the world does that accomplish? My husband and I wanted to order different sides and I wanted a salad as a first course. It was a huge waste of money. The hotel's only redeeming quality is that it is close to the main sidewalk as opposed to being set back like Caesar's. I would not stay here again.	
Sep 8 2009 	Great hotel.... we were very pleased!	My husband and I stayed at the Monte Carlo in August and had a great stay! The hotel was very accomodating and let us check into our room at 11:30am. The room was spacious and was very clean. We had a pool view and didn't find that the music was very loud like other travelers have mentioned. The great thing about this hotel is that it has a food court! They have Subway, Starbucks, McDonald's, Rubio's, and a quick Chinese food place. It is so nice to have a convenient and cheap place to grab a snack when you are hungry. Also, you are ALLOWED to bring food items from the food court into the pool area!! So save your cash on that $5 diet coke poolside and bring in a cup from McDonald's. People were also &quot;spiking&quot; their drinks before they walked into the pool area since the attendents at the pool will ask to review your bag. Drinks poolside are around $18 to give you an idea. Hope that this review helps! :)	
