Aug 6 2009 	OK but I would stay somewhere else	The hotel was fine, we aren't very picky travelers.The room was a little substandard, as it was on a low floor which faced the loading dock. The dock had trucks backing up all night with their beeping and honking. We had already fully unpacked before we realized this problem so didn't ask to be moved. The hotel was half empty so I am not sure why they put folks in these rooms as they have to be aware of the issue. If you find yourself facing the dock, then before you unpack go ask to change rooms so you can sleep (day or night depending on how much fun you plan on having).The room itself was nice, and we got a good rate. The buffet is fairly expensive and they don't have the &quot;all-day&quot; deal that many of the other hotels have to make it cheaper. The selection is a lot, but in Vegas terms it was substandard... we had eaten in the Luxor and Mandalay Bay buffets and found them much better.The wave pool and lazy river are nice but they are pretty darn packed with people. The staff said the hotel was fairly empty but you couldn't move at the pool so I wouldn't want to be there when the hotel is full. Also, there are a lot of folks drinking beer in the water all day but not a lot of people getting out to go to the bathroom.... a little gross when you consider how packed it was. If you want a drink you can't flag down a waitress and have to spend the better part of an hour in a line-up at the bar.The location is right in the middle of the strip but it is not handy at all to the monorail as it is right between two stations. You walk a lot in Vegas regardless so I would suggest finding a place that has handy access to the monorail. We ended up on one end of the strip after a long day and decided to get a taxi back to the hotel... that ate up any savings we got from getting a good rate.They have a business centre but the rate for internet is crazy! Bring your laptop and find a wifi spot if you think you need to be plugged in.All in all... OK place, nothing to bring you back again rather than trying out a different hotel.	
