Jul 22 2009 	Great accomodations at an affordable price	For one of the older hotels on the strip it was very clean and has been nicely renovated. Unlike some of the earlier reviews we did not experience any issues with construction noise. Our check in and check out were very easy and the room was as promised in the reservations. We found it to be very convenient to have a Starbucks and a few fast food places in the hotel for early morning and late night snacks. Probably the highlight of our stay was the wonderful pool or I should say pools at the Monte Carlo. It was nice to have the option of a wave pool, a lazy river, and a regular pool to lounge in. One tip for you pool bums are to buy the larger souvenir cups the first day at the pool and reuse them the rest of the time you are there. You will get twice the amount of beverage for a little more than you would pay for a smaller one. Also the one time we ordered food while at the pool it was brought out in a timely manner and was very yummy. Just be careful when charging to your room because you could experience some sticker shock by the end of the week. Out of our whole stay the only negative thing we did find is that the room service is slow on cleaning the food trays left in the halls. The spa facilities at the hotel are well worth a visit. In specific the hot stone massage was awesome - make sure you ask for Christina.	
