Jul 6 2009 	Great Stay- Pool makes it all worth it!	We were hesitant to book this hotel for a 3 night stay over the 4th of July weekend. I feel that this review is needed to balance the bad reviews. Our experience was great. Overall, the staff was very helpful and friendly, the hotel room (while fairly basic and small) was clean and had a nice view of the srip. We stayed in a deluxe high floor strip view room and it was quiet and the beds were fine. The pool was the best part! You do have to get there early to get a chair- if you do, you should have no problems finding chairs together.Pro's- Wave pool- while kind of small, it is lots of fun- The lazy river is swift and fun- You can bring your own raft to the pool. You can also rent one of their rafts, but it's cheaper to buy one at walgreens which is nearby. The pool attendants are also happy to blow it up for you- again, very good service- Pool drink service was fast and someone always came by. The food by the pool was also good.- There's a regular pool as well- mainly adults in this pool. We had a 6 year old with us, so we used the wave pool and lazy river mainly.- Pool area can get croweded, but don't let that deter you- it's fine- Pool hours are the same in most of the big hotels- this one closes at 7. Some others close at 6 (it's vegas, go figure)- Live DJ at the pool. The music is loud, but not terrible. Even with a hangover you should be ok.- There's a store in the lobby- has all your essentials you could need- Food court in the hotel (McDonalds, Starbucks, Rubios, etc)- great for a quick bite- Fast elevators- easy check-in and check-out- fast valet service- pretty good location on the strip- especially if traveling with kids- it's close to excalibur and M&amp;M world, etcCon's:- Room pretty small, but adequate- Halls could use some touching up- Room service trays left out for a few days- Food and service at their cafe was just ok- and prices pretty high- Casino was ok- I've been to better and worseAll in all