Apr 15 2009 	The place to stay for elegant style great service in Vegas!	We chose to stay at the Monte Carlo out of all Vegas hotels, since we got a great deal and it was in a decent location on the strip. The hotel was very clean with an elegant decor. Overall the casino floor was much quieter than some of the overcrowded ones at Bellagio and Caesars. We came to appreciate this quietness after seeing the hustle and bustle that is Vegas.There is a very convenient food court right near the hotel rooms area, consisting of: Starbucks, Subway, McD's, Manchu Wok, and Rubios. Great for a quick bite or snack.We stayed in the Monaco Suite, which was just lovely. Our room faced the side of the hotel (toward Excalibur) so we were away from the construction noise that is currently going on with the development of the City Center complex on the other side. Be sure to request a room away from the construction, unless you want to be woken up at 6am every day. The room was spotless and had a very modern appeal with dark furniture, a king bed, a suede couch, a floor-length mirror, 2 bathrooms, flat panel tv, and calming blue-gray walls. No complaints about the room at all - it was great!The location of the hotel is not as center strip as one would imagine. It's right next to New York, New York and somewhat diagonal from Planet Hollywood, but the blocks are SO HUGE in Vegas that it takes forever to walk anywhere. I would probably stay north of Planet Hollywood next time, because that's where I spent most of my time (Bellagio, Caesars, Venetian, etc). Don't get me wrong though, Monte Carlo is a beautiful hotel that I think is sometimes overlooked. They offer some great pricing, so definitely worth staying at if you're on a budget!	
