Mar 28 2009 	noisy pool noisy construction otherwise OK	My husband and I stayed here on 17-20th March. The rooms are fine and the location, in the middle of the south end of the strip, is good. Also the whole place isn't large by Vegas standards, so its not too far to walk to anywhere and is not too disorientating for a first-time traveller to Vegas. However right now the new CityCenter project is being constructed right next door and the construction goes on all night. It is extremely noisy and we were woken repeatedly. I would not recommend staying here until the CityCenter project is complete, unless you are deaf. The other problem was the pool - all Vega hotel pools pump music through speakers into their pool areas (without leaving even one little quiet corner) but the music at the Monte Carlo was blaring. It was more like a club. No way we could read a book or listen to an MP3 player while lying by the pool - we just gave up after about an hour. On the up side, we only ate once at the buffet (for breakfast) but would definitely recommend the breakfast buffet - it's in a nice room, well managed, with tasty and quality food, a bargain for the price.	
