Mar 18 2009 	Very comfortable.	Overall this is a great place to stay. Check in was a breeze. We arrived at noon and they had several rooms available immediately. We had a choice of pool view, strip view or mountain view. We opted for the pool view, but once we got into the room you could hear the noise of construction so we changed to a much quieter mountain view. You should ask about construction noise when checking in. Rooms were very clean and comfortable. I was nervious after reading a review aobut bed bugs. After careful inspection and 3 nights later, there were no signs of any bed bugs or any other bugs.We booked a stay and play package, good value but probably would have been better off taking the AAA rate. They offered $20.00 in food court coupons. Keep in mind these are not vouchers. You order something and you get a free pop or free tortia chips. Not much of a savings and you won't use all the coupons. It also came with 2 buffet vouchers. This is worth between $20 &amp; $40 depending on the meal. The buffet was okay but you felt obligated to use them when there are so many other choices in Vegas.The food court was nice &amp; reasonable. McDonalds, Pizza, Mexican, Chinese, Starbucks and Hagendaz. There is also a reasonably priced Pub and mexican restaurant Diablo's. Diablo's was always busy with $3.00 drink specials from 3-7p.m. Temperatures didn't allow us to enjoy the pool. We did take a walk to the pool. It is a very nice area with one main pool, a lazy river and a wave pool. We did enjoy the casino's. We don't spend a lot of money gambeling but we did enjoy the monopoly game. This casino seemed to have the best payouts. We couldn't win anything any where else. The main pool water was very chilly....not heated. Location was good. Walking distance to many of the main hotels, casino's and shows. Across the street was a 1/2 off ticket booth for shows. This had the shortest lines of the 3 boots. Don't go to the one next to the M&amp;M store or Bills. Those lines were very long. I did learn that you don't get your &quot;real&quot; tickets here. Once you pay for your show you are directed to the venue where the show is to pick up your &quot;real&quot; tickets with seat assignment. This hotel isn't as plush as the Bellagio and the rooms aren't as big, but it is a very good value. If you are looking for the basic ammenities and not the most expensive restaurants and shops this is a great place to stay.	
