Mar 3 2009 	Fun Hotel with One Exception	I stayed at the Monte Carlo Hotel and Casino on March 2, 2009, with my wife, my brother and his wife. We were in town to see The Beatles Love at the Mirage. Overall I would give the Monte Carlo very positive reviews. I like the Monte Carlo because the casino is fairly small by strip standards and not so hard to find people or lengthy walks to get places. The casino was very nice, clean and very good drink service. The rooms were nice and clean. Diablos Cantina was a lot of fun during Happy Hour with crazy drink specials with the female bartender pouring wild shots while standing on the bar. My only complaint involved an incident at the Cafe and involves something that would have never happened in Vegas 15 years ago before the whole town went corporate. After we returned from the show at the Mirage we went for a quick bite to eat the Cafe before going to bed. While we were in the process of being seated the hostess had a fight with three servers right in front of our table over who was going to be our server. We waited for about 10 minutes and no one even brought water to our table or took our drink orders. If the cafe had been busy I would have understood, but it was close to 90% empty. I called over the hostess to ask if there was a problem and she said someone would be with us shortly. We waited a few more minutes and still no one came to our table to even bring us water, let along take our food order. I then complained rather sternly to the manager about what the problem was with the service. She informed me that if I did not calm down she was going to call security and have me removed. This despite the fact that we had been waiting for 15 minutes with no assurance we would get water let alone dinner. I told her this level of service was not acceptable and she told me that she would not speak to me until I calmed down. I saved her the trouble and our party just left the cafe. 15 years ago that would never have happened in Vegas and is now one of the reasons I go to Laughlin now rather than Vegas. 15 years ago that manager would have go to the kitchen themselves to get the water and probably comped our meals. But in these modern times where these corporate casinos have to squeeze every dime out of every possible source of cash in the hotels customer service has to take a hit. So instead of taking care of us, the manager was complete rude and disrepectful to me and probably cost her resturant $100 that night. In the grand scheme of things that doesn't matter to the Monte Carlo, but it demonstrates how much Las Vegas has changed and not for the better.	
Mar 3 2009 	Much better than expected	We stayed here for the Valentine's weekend. It was much better than expected after reading some of these reviews and we would stay here again forsure! We got the deal from Westjet with 2 free buffets (AMAZING!), 2 drinks and 2 spa passes. We only used the buffet. We also got $10 slot money with the package on top of the $10 for signing up for the MGM card. (The casinos in Old Vegas only give free cards or entry forms for signing up.) The fast food places were ok, but a little expensive. The room was very nice (especially compared to Stratosphere), the service was great, and the casino had very loose slots. It was the only casino I won in. I also won the free trip to Cancun that the casino in Old Vegas draws each night, but the trip was not free. It would cost over $300 in taxes and fees. We asked for a room away from the construction and we got a room on the 27th floor. We did not hear a thing, and the beds were very comfy. We saw the V-Show after getting a cheap ticket from a timeshare promo. It was good for $10 but not worth a full price ticket. If you are going to see a show, but the tix for half price on the street. Just get in line early in the morning. We also went fishing in Lake Mead with a guide and it was AMAZING! We caught 23 fish in 5 hours. It is only 30min away from the strip. The wax museum was ok, but not really worth the price of the ticket and the aquarium at Mandalay Bay was not cheap but very good.We will definately stay at the Monte Carlo again. Our stay was great! Thanks!!	
