Feb 20 2009 	Great Comps	We spent a long Valentine's weekend and were very happy with the hotel and it's services. Checked in around noon and got a room immediately. Room was clean and bed comfortable. I am a smoker and did find there wasn't much ventilation to get rid of the smoke. Window opened about 6&quot; but that didn't help much and no exhaust fan in the bathroom. Also thought the bedspreads and carpet were outdated but I didn't expect (or pay the price of) the Wynn. We had a corner room and could still hear hall noise but never heard any construction noise. Shower was amazing. The location is convenient with MGM and New York, New York within close walking distance. Also nice to have Walgreen's and CVS within a block for those forgotten items. Food at the Cafe and the Buffet were both very good. We found casino staff to be very friendly and comps from their Players Club were amazing. All of our food charges were comped ($150+) which was a surprise since we are not big gamblers. We will definitely stay at Monte Carlo again.	
