Feb 3 2009 	Exceeded My Expectations	Due to numerous negative posts about the Monte Carlo I had set my expectations fairly low. However, I was very pleasantly surprised at my stay. The check-in was quick, friendly and accurate, and all the perks of the package I reserved were noted and offered.The room was very, very nice and the bathroom was roomy. Everything was clean and fresh in appearance and smell. The housekeeping staff restocked and refreshed the room very well each day.Yes, there is construction next door and they do work 24 hours a day. But I was never bothered by any noise whatsoever. Occassional banging or a horn were insignificant and would never prevent me from sleeping comfortably. I've got to assume it was more quiet and less bright than the flash of the Strip, had my room faced that direction.I will admit the walls are very thin and a noisy neighbor &quot;could&quot; be a problem very easily. I was fortunate that my neighbors were quiet so no problem there.The food was good at the restaurants and buffet, and even the food court would be great for someone who just wants to spend a couple bucks on food or a soda (even the McDonalds had a few items for $1).Didn't do terribly well on the slots at Monte Carlo, compared to other casinos, but that's Lady Luck, not the establishment so much.Checkout was efficient and accurate.All in all, I would definitely stay at Monte Carlo again. Previous negative reports are helpful but remember that some people only see the bad side of everything. There is definitely very little &quot;bad&quot; about the Monte Carlo so don't be afraid at all.	
